cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI 

This paper deals with handwritten text recognition using convolutional LSTM neural networks, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of data augmentation and ensemble learning, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the deployment of the proposed approach in a search engine, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR).
